description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The Mid Yorkshire Hospitals NHS Trust are looking for an enthusiastic, dynamic and motivated Pharmacy Technician to join our Medicines Optimisation Team either as a Band 4 or Band 5, depending on experience.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;This exciting development role will enable the successful candidate to receive training and demonstrate competence whilst supporting the efficient delivery of pharmacy services to wards across the trust. This role would be equally suited to any level of medicines optimisation experience, making this an ideal route for pharmacy technicians to develop skills in a hospital setting.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;On successful completion of a specified development framework the candidate will be uplifted to the role of Pharmacy Technician Higher Level – Medicines Optimisation (AfC Band 5).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;The post involves joining the Pharmacy Medicines Optimisation Team at ward level whilst receiving training and undertaking validations to contribute to the following tasks: &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;•Reconciling patient’s medication history&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;•Assessing the suitability for re-use of patients’ own medication&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;•Ordering cost-effective and appropriate supplies of medicinal products&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;•Supporting Near-patient dispensing initiatives by undertaking dispensing or accuracy checking of prescriptions&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;•Managing medicines at discharge&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;•Working within a multidisciplinary team&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;•Patient counselling&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;•Supporting new and trainee staff as and when required.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The applicant must demonstrate an ability to receive training, develop in line with a specified framework, work methodically, with meticulous attention to detail and be able to communicate well with other healthcare professionals, patients and relatives whilst overcoming any barriers to understanding. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;It is extremely important that the applicant works in line with the current standards for pharmacy professionals, as well as in agreement to the trusts own values and behaviours, which are, caring, improving, respect, and high standards.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The Pharmacy Team at The Mid Yorkshire Hospitals NHS Trust is friendly, supportive and welcoming. We will support the successful candidate with their introduction into this role, their development to Pharmacy Technician Higher Level and with their ongoing professional development for revalidation with the GPhC.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;The applicant must be registered as a Pharmacy Technician with the GPhC and hold an NVQ Level 3 in Pharmaceutical services, BTEC in Pharmaceutical sciences (or equivalent). The applicant must also hold a Certificate of Accreditation as an Accuracy Checking Technician (or equivalent) or be eligible and willing to work towards gaining this qualification.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;The applicant should possess initiative and be confident to work independently and as part of a team interchangeably. They should have excellent communication, organisational and prioritising skills. They must be adaptable to the needs of the Pharmacy Service, which may involve working across all sites of The Mid Yorkshire Hospitals Trust and also support flexible working patterns to meet the needs of patients and to support efficient delivery of the service in line with current NHS initiatives towards 7 day services.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;For further information or an informal discussion about the role contact: &lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Charlotte Wright, Specialist Pharmacy Technician:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;charlotte.wright30@nhs.net or on 01924 543848&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
